Task 1
Using the cd and mkdir commands create the following directory tree in your home directory
(in any subdirectory), or directly in ~):

ukos
|\ katalog
|      |\ katalog2
| \ katalog3
 \ klamka

I use commands :
mkdir ukos (mkdir - this command creating directories)
cd ukos
mkdir katalog
mkdir klamka
cd katalog
mkdir katalog2
mkdir katalog3

Task 2
In directory ukos\klamka create files zajecia2.txt zajecia2.log inny.txt nowy.txt

I use commands :
touch zajecia2.txt
touch zajecia2.log
touch inny.txt
touch nowy.txt

Task 3
Use one command mkdir and creat in directory ukos following directory:
ukos/to/jest/dluga/nazwa

I use command:
mkdir -p ././ukos/to/jest/dluga/nazwa

Task 4
Set in directory ukos/to/jest/dluga/nazwa file dane.txt

I use command:
touch dane.txt

Task 5
Delete from directory ukos/klamka every files with .txt extension

I use command:
rm /home/ubuntu/ukos/klamka/*.txt

Delete directory ukos/katalog/katalog2

I use command:
rmdir katalog/katalog1

Delete entire director klamka by using single command.

I use command:
rm -r ukos
